President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 1-7, 2016, as National Charter Schools Week. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of high-quality public charter schools in providing educational opportunities for underserved communities. These schools have the flexibility to develop innovative methods of education and can serve as models for other institutions. However, Obama also emphasizes the need for accountability and high standards in charter schools. He praises the educators working in these schools and reaffirms the commitment to ensuring all students have access to an excellent education. The proclamation calls on states and communities to support charter schools and the students they serve.